00:32:04.280 --> 00:32:05.610
So we'll wait.

00:32:05.610 --> 00:32:08.360
This, by the way, is a method
which is used for integration.

00:32:08.360 --> 00:32:11.580
But it was invented to do
something with Laplace

00:32:11.580 --> 00:32:14.410
transforms and inversion
of certain kinds of

00:32:14.410 --> 00:32:15.600
differential equations.

00:32:15.600 --> 00:32:17.020
By heavy side.

00:32:17.020 --> 00:32:21.530
And so it came much later
than integration.

00:32:21.530 --> 00:32:26.360
But anyway, it's a very
convenient method.

00:32:26.360 --> 00:32:30.210
So here's the set up
with this one.

00:32:30.210 --> 00:32:34.440
Again, we want a term for
this (x - 1) factor.

00:32:34.440 --> 00:32:36.690
And now we're going to also
have a term with the

00:32:36.690 --> 00:32:39.120
denominator x squared plus 1.

00:32:39.120 --> 00:32:40.760
But this is the difference.

00:32:40.760 --> 00:32:44.590
It's now going to be a first
degree polynomial.

00:32:44.590 --> 00:32:53.040
One degree down from
the quadratic here.

00:32:53.040 --> 00:32:55.620
So this is what I keep
on calling the setup,

