00:44:27.860 --> 00:44:30.040
So let's handle this thing.

00:44:30.040 --> 00:44:34.240
What if the degree of P is
bigger than or equal to the

00:44:34.240 --> 00:44:42.810
degree of Q. That's the thing
that I claimed was easier.

00:44:42.810 --> 00:44:45.880
And I'm going to describe
to you how it's done.

00:44:45.880 --> 00:44:49.990
Now, in analogy, with numbers
you might call this an

00:44:49.990 --> 00:44:55.070
improper fraction.

00:44:55.070 --> 00:45:00.100
That's the thing that should
echo in your mind when you're

00:45:00.100 --> 00:45:01.970
thinking about this.

00:45:01.970 --> 00:45:04.600
And I'm just going to do
it by example here.

00:45:04.600 --> 00:45:08.860
Let's see., I cooked up an
example so that I don't make

00:45:08.860 --> 00:45:11.220
an arithmetistic mistake
along the way.

00:45:11.220 --> 00:45:16.990
So there are two or three steps
that I need to explain.

00:45:16.990 --> 00:45:18.030
So here's an example.

00:45:18.030 --> 00:45:21.320
The denominator's degree 2,
the numerator is degree 3.

00:45:21.320 --> 00:45:24.610
It well exceeds, so there's
a problem here.

00:45:24.610 --> 00:45:27.880
Our method is not
going to work.

00:45:27.880 --> 00:45:32.620
And the first step that I
want to carry out is to

00:45:32.620 --> 00:45:36.370
reverse Step 1.

00:45:36.370 --> 00:45:38.940
That is, I don't want the
factorization for what I'm

00:45:38.940 --> 00:45:39.620
going to do next.

00:45:39.620 --> 00:45:42.040
I want it multiplied out.

00:45:42.040 --> 00:45:44.230
That means I have to multiply
through, so I

00:45:44.230 --> 00:45:48.670
get x ^2 + x - 2.

00:45:48.670 --> 00:45:52.980
I'm back to the starting
place here.

00:45:52.980 --> 00:45:57.115
And now, the next thing that I'm
going to do is, I'm going

00:45:57.115 --> 00:46:01.130
to use long division.

00:46:01.130 --> 00:46:03.400
That's how you convert
an improper

00:46:03.400 --> 00:46:07.530
fraction to a proper fraction.

00:46:07.530 --> 00:46:12.710
This is something you were
supposed to learn in, I don't

00:46:12.710 --> 00:46:16.780
know, Grade 4, I know.

00:46:16.780 --> 00:46:23.970
Grade 3, Grade 4, Grade
5, Grade 6, etc.

00:46:23.970 --> 00:46:27.560
So here's how it works in
the case of polynomials.

00:46:27.560 --> 00:46:31.030
It's kind of amusing.

00:46:31.030 --> 00:46:37.760
So we're dividing this
polynomial into that one.

00:46:37.760 --> 00:46:41.950
And so the quotient to first
order here is x.

00:46:41.950 --> 00:46:44.710
That is, that's going to match
the top terms. So I get

00:46:44.710 --> 00:46:48.500
x^3 + x ^2 - 2x.

00:46:48.500 --> 00:46:50.310
That's the product.

00:46:50.310 --> 00:46:51.890
And now I subtract.

00:46:51.890 --> 00:46:53.990
And it cancels.

00:46:53.990 --> 00:46:58.440
So we get here - x ^2 + 2x.

00:46:58.440 --> 00:47:01.110
That's the difference.

00:47:01.110 --> 00:47:04.260
And now I need to divide
this next term in.

00:47:04.260 --> 00:47:08.190
And I need a - 1.

00:47:08.190 --> 00:47:14.700
So - 1 times this is
- x ^2 - x + 2.

00:47:14.700 --> 00:47:16.260
And I subtract.

00:47:16.260 --> 00:47:17.800
And the x^2's cancel.

00:47:17.800 --> 00:47:24.210
And here I get + 3x - 2.

00:47:24.210 --> 00:47:27.090
Now, this thing has a name.

00:47:27.090 --> 00:47:30.880
This is called the quotient.

00:47:30.880 --> 00:47:33.090
And this thing also
has a name.

00:47:33.090 --> 00:47:39.070
This is called the remainder.

00:47:39.070 --> 00:47:43.960
And now I'll show you how it
works by sticking it into the

00:47:43.960 --> 00:47:44.560
answer here.

00:47:44.560 --> 00:47:47.250
The quotient is x - 1.

00:47:47.250 --> 00:47:51.000
And the remainder is, let's
get down there.

00:47:51.000 --> 00:47:58.820
3x - 2 / x ^2 + x - 2.

00:47:58.820 --> 00:48:03.110
So the punchline here
is that this

00:48:03.110 --> 00:48:05.450
thing is easy to integrate.

00:48:05.450 --> 00:48:08.190
This is easy.

00:48:08.190 --> 00:48:17.460
And this one, you can use, now
you can use cover-up, The

00:48:17.460 --> 00:48:18.480
method that we had before.

00:48:18.480 --> 00:48:21.490
Because the degree of the
numerator is now below the

00:48:21.490 --> 00:48:22.700
degree of the denominator.

00:48:22.700 --> 00:48:25.920
It's now first degree and
this is second degree.

00:48:25.920 --> 00:48:27.960
What you can't do is
use cover-up to

00:48:27.960 --> 00:48:29.950
start out with here.

00:48:29.950 --> 00:48:32.630
That will give you
the wrong answer.

